Note:
Task #462 gate test: `joined with` auto-stringification of provably-Integer
operands (owner-ruled 2026-06-11).

`X joined with Y` desugars to string_concat(X, Y). Before #462, an Integer
VALUE operand was read as a char* by the concat and crashed (or silently
produced garbage; 0 printed as empty). The stage1 codegen now rewrites any
operand it can PROVE is Integer-valued into integer_to_string(operand)
before the concat. Proof sources covered here:

  Case 1: integer literal operand            -> stringified
  Case 2: variable initialized from a literal -> stringified
  Case 3: arithmetic binary-op result         -> stringified
  Case 4: string-string join                  -> unchanged (no stringify)
  Case 5: literal 0                           -> prints "0", not empty
  Case 6: proven-Integer variable on the LEFT -> stringified
  Case 7: String-typed variable               -> unchanged (no stringify)
  Case 8: negative value through a variable   -> stringified with sign

Assertions go through string_equals on the concat results, per the
canonical tests/test_utils.runa convention. Exits 0 with "ALL TESTS
PASSED" when every case holds.
:End Note

Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as T
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as Str

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be T.create_test_results()
    T.begin_suite(results, "compiler.joined_with_integer")

    Note: Case 1: integer literal operand is stringified.
    Let r1 be "count: " joined with 42
    Let eq1 be proc string_equals from Str with r1, "count: 42"
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 1: literal join", eq1, 1)

    Note: Case 2: variable whose initializer is an integer literal carries
    Note: Integer proof and is stringified.
    Let n be 7
    Let r2 be "n=" joined with n
    Let eq2 be proc string_equals from Str with r2, "n=7"
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 2: Integer-var join", eq2, 1)

    Note: Case 3: arithmetic binary-op result is Integer proof. The
    Note: multiplicative form binds the whole product into the right-hand
    Note: operand of joined with (joined with parses a multiplicative
    Note: expression on the right).
    Let r3 be "sum=" joined with n multiplied by 3
    Let eq3 be proc string_equals from Str with r3, "sum=21"
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 3: arithmetic join", eq3, 1)

    Note: Case 4: string-string join is unchanged by the rewrite.
    Let r4 be "a" joined with "b"
    Let eq4 be proc string_equals from Str with r4, "ab"
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 4: string-string unchanged", eq4, 1)

    Note: Case 5: literal 0 must print as "0", not as the empty string the
    Note: pre-#462 pointer-read produced.
    Let r5 be "z=" joined with 0
    Let eq5 be proc string_equals from Str with r5, "z=0"
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 5: zero prints 0", eq5, 1)

    Note: Case 6: proven-Integer variable as the LEFT operand is also
    Note: stringified (the rewrite inspects both arguments of the desugared
    Note: string_concat call).
    Let r6 be n joined with "x"
    Let eq6 be proc string_equals from Str with r6, "7x"
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 6: Integer left operand", eq6, 1)

    Note: Case 7: a String-typed variable carries no Integer proof and is
    Note: passed through untouched.
    Let s be "hi"
    Let r7 be "p-" joined with s
    Let eq7 be proc string_equals from Str with r7, "p-hi"
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 7: String var unchanged", eq7, 1)

    Note: Case 8: a negative Integer value reaches integer_to_string with
    Note: its sign intact. Computed through a variable because a bare
    Note: `joined with 0 minus 5` would bind as (join result) minus 5 at
    Note: the additive precedence level.
    Let m be 0 minus 5
    Let r8 be "neg=" joined with m
    Let eq8 be proc string_equals from Str with r8, "neg=-5"
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 8: negative value join", eq8, 1)

    Note: Case 9 (task #477): a BARE `Display <Integer>` of zero must emit the
    Note: digit "0", not the empty string. Pre-#477 the codegen-emitted
    Note: print_integer zero path left %rsi pointing past the '0' onto the null
    Note: terminator (the shared .convert_done incq overshot), so print_integer(0)
    Note: wrote a zero-length string. The Display statements below print "0" on
    Note: its own line followed by a sentinel; the human/CI golden diff and the
    Note: standalone test_display_integer_zero.runa cover the textual output.
    Note: Here we assert the in-process-comparable equivalent: zero round-trips
    Note: through the same value-to-text proof model via joined with.
    Let zr be "z=" joined with 0
    Let eqz be proc string_equals from Str with zr, "z=0"
    T.assert_equal(results, "Case 9: bare-integer zero stringifies", eqz, 1)
    Display 0
    Display "(bare Display 0 above must show a digit, not a blank line)"

    T.print_summary(results)
    Let exit_code be T.get_failed(results)
    T.destroy_test_results(results)
    Return exit_code
End Process
